1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 {This is the soundest reply.} cxd4 5. exd4 
a6 6. Nf3 {Played by Rapport.} Bg4 7. h3 Bxf3 8. Qxf3 {Most players would prefer 
White though Black is solid.} Nc6 9. O-O-O e6 10. g4 Bb4 {[%cal Bb4c3,Bf6e4]} 
11. Ne2 {Not giving Black any opportunity to play ...Bxc3.} Qa5 {[%cal 
Ga5a2][%csl Ra2]} 12. Kb1 {[%cal Gb1a2]} Ne4 13. Nc1 {[%cal Bc1b3]} Bd6 14. Nb3 
Qc7 15. Be3 O-O 16. Rg1 {[%cal Bg4g5,Bf1d3] A good prophylactic move. White 
anticipates Black will reinforce the e4-Knight with ...f5 soon, after which 
White can exchange on f5 and get an open g-file for his Rook.} b5 17. Bd3 f5 
{There it is!} 18. gxf5 {[%cal Gg1g7]} exf5 19. Bh6 $18 {[%cal 
Gh6g7,Gg1g7,Gf3f5,Gf3d5][%csl Rg7,Rf5,Rd5] Rapport,R (2704) -Sutovsky,E (2624) 
Tromsoe ol (Men) 41st 2014 (9.4) 1-0. The rest of this game can be seen in the 
model game section of the main course.} *

