1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 {Already taking Black out of mainline theory! This does seem 
similar to a very popular opening, The Italian Game, with 1 e4 e5 2 ♘f3 and 3 
♘c4. We are doing that, but with 1 d4!} d5 3. Bf4 g6 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 {This is 
generally what we play against ...g6 setups. White is well placed to advance the 
h-pawn.} O-O 6. h5 {[%cal Gh1h7][%csl Rg8,Rh8,Rh7] This is the most aggressive 
and best move after Black played 5... O-O. I think Black is inviting trouble. 
White has to be prepared to sacrifice an exchange, but it's well worth it.} Nxh5 
$6 {This is the type of position which a computer might be able to hold as Black 
but it requires very accurate defence which is well beyond the powers of most 
people.} 7. Rxh5 gxh5 8. Qxh5 {White's plan is not subtle but it doesn't need to 
be. It's a direct attack on Black's King. Currently Black only has his 
dark-squared Bishop defending the King. If he has any realistic chance of 
surviving he will need to bring in reinforcements and blunt White's threats.} 
Nd7 {[%cal Bd7f6] Bringing the Knight quickly to f6 makes a lot of sense to me 
but I can't find any games in my database where it has been played. 
Understandably not many black players accept the sacrifice and those that have 
done so have a very poor record.} 9. Qh2 $1 {[%cal Gh2c7,Bf1d3,Bg1f3,Be1c1][%csl 
Gh2,Rc7,Gf4] This move not only attacks the c7-pawn, but also repositions the 
Queen such that Black won't be able to play ...Nf6 with gain of tempo.} c6 10. 
Bd3 {[%cal Gd3h7,Gh2h7][%csl Rh7] Already threatening mate.} Nf6 $16 {This feels 
like Black's best shot at holding this position, but White still has a wealth of 
good moves such as Nf3, O-O-O and Rh1.} 11. Nf3 {One nice idea to point out here 
is the following line.} Bg4 12. Ne5 {[%cal Ge5g4][%csl Rg4]} Bh5 {Black is 
attempting to block White's attack with ...Bg6, but White can play as follows:} 
13. Bxh7+ Kxh7 (13... Nxh7 {is met by} 14. Qxh5 {when White is a pawn up and 
still has a strong attack.}) 14. g4 $16 {[%cal Gh2h7,Be1c1,Ba1h1,Gg4h5][%csl 
Rh5,Rh7] This ensures that the lines of attack remain very much open. I think 
White is objectively better and in a practical game Black's position is very 
difficult to defend.} *

